1155","1254":"1254","10 December 1248":"10 december 1248","about 1254":"circa 1254","about 1174":"circa 1174","1208":"1208","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Muncaster Church, Muncaster, Cumberland, England":"Muncaster, Cumberland, England","England":"England","Muncaster, Copeland Borough, Cumbria, England":"Muncaster, Cumberland, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Bebington, Cheshire, England":"Bebington, Cheshire, England"},"en":{"about 1174–about 1254":"about 1174–about 1254","1174–1254":"1174–1254","1174–1240":"1174–1240","1160–1208":"1160–1208","1191–1277":"1191–1277","1196–1277":"1196–1277","1200–1248":"1200–1248","1155–1254":"1155–1254","1196":"1196","1240":"1240","1174":"1174","1160":"1160","1191":"1191","1215":"1215","1248":"1248","Abt 1194":"about 1194","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1277":"1277","1155":"1155","1254":"1254","10 December 1248":"10 December 1248","about 1254":"about 1254","about 1174":"about 1174","1208":"1208","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Muncaster Church, Muncaster, Cumberland, England":"Muncaster, Cumberland, England","England":"England","Muncaster, Copeland Borough, Cumbria, England":"Muncaster, Cumberland, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Bebington, Cheshire, England":"Bebington, Cheshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Longville","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Longueville-la-Gifart, now Longueville-sur-Scie (Seine-Maritime, France)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":41,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":50,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes de Longville was born about 1174, in Bebington, Cheshire, England as the daughter of John de Longville. She married Ranulph de Oxton about 1194, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died about 1254, in Lancashire, England, at the age of 82."},"et":{"about 1174–about 1254":"umbes 1174–umbes 1254","1174–1254":"1174–1254","1174–1240":"1174–1240","1160–1208":"1160–1208","1191–1277":"1191–1277","1196–1277":"1196–1277","1200–1248":"1200–1248","1155–1254":"1155–1254","1196":"1196","1240":"1240","1174":"1174","1160":"1160","1191":"1191","1215":"1215","1248":"1248","Abt 1194":"umbes 1194","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1277":"1277","1155":"1155","1254":"1254","10 December 1248":"10. detsember 1248","about 1254":"umbes 1254","about 1174":"umbes 1174","1208":"1208","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Muncaster Church, Muncaster, Cumberland, England":"Muncaster, Cumberland, England","England":"England","Muncaster, Copeland Borough, Cumbria, England":"Muncaster, Cumberland, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Bebington, Cheshire, England":"Bebington, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1174–about 1254":"noin 1174–noin 1254","1174–1254":"1174–1254","1174–1240":"1174–1240","1160–1208":"1160–1208","1191–1277":"1191–1277","1196–1277":"1196–1277","1200–1248":"1200–1248","1155–1254":"1155–1254","1196":"1196","1240":"1240","1174":"1174","1160":"1160","1191":"1191","1215":"1215","1248":"1248","Abt 1194":"noin 1194","1224":"1224","1200":"1200","1277":"1277","1155":"1155","1254":"1254","10 December 1248":"10. joulukuuta 1248","about 1254":"noin 1254","about 1174":"noin 1174","1208":"1208","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Muncaster Church, Muncaster, Cumberland, England":"Muncaster, Cumberland, England","England":"England","Muncaster, Copeland Borough, Cumbria, England":"Muncaster, Cumberland, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Bebington, Cheshire, England":"Bebington, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"about